# Process Flow Diagrams (PFD)

This folder contains the main Process Flow Diagrams developed for the conceptual design of the ammonium sulfate production plant.

Two diagrams were created to represent different sections of the process.

## PFD S-100 – Outdoor Process Section

This diagram represents the outdoor processing area where the main chemical operations take place.

The equipment in this section operates as closed process units and does not require a controlled indoor environment.

Main operations include:

- Reaction processes
- Mixing systems
- Heat exchange
- Pumps and compressors
- Granulation stage for ammonium sulfate production

## PFD S-200 – Indoor Processing Section

This diagram represents the indoor section of the plant where downstream processing and handling operations take place.

These operations require a controlled environment for product handling and operational safety.

Typical operations in this section include:

- Drying and conditioning of granules
- Product handling
- Storage and packaging preparation
